<div class = 'img'><a href = 'http://martinfowler.com/articles/badri-hexagonal'><img src = 'http://martinfowler.com/snips/badri.jpg' width = '100px;' height = '' alt = '' title = ''/></a></div><p><a href="https://twitter.com/badrij">Badri Janakiraman</a> and I continue <a href="http://martinfowler.com/articles/badri-hexagonal">our video conversation about hexagonal Rails</a> by looking into how we should work with the Rails framework. We posit that when you work with a framework like Rails you should decide to either treat it as a platform, meaning you embrace it into your application, or as suite of components, treating each aspect as an independently replaceable unit.</p>
